    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9502" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρίσσω</span></b> , aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔφριξεν</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρίξᾱς</span>, perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πεφρί̄κᾱσι</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-υῖαι</span>: grow rough,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bristle</span>, as the fields with grain, the battle-field
          with spears, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.599</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.339</span></i>; the wild boar as to his back
          or crest, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λοφιήν, νῶτον, τ 446</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.473</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shudder, shudder
            at</span> (cf. ‘goose-flesh’), <i><span class="en">Il.
            11.383</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          24.775</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
